2
00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:30.673
♪ Don't be. be. be afraid ♪

3
00:01:31.382 --> 00:01:35.637
♪ Don't be. be. be. be. be afraid ♪

4
00:01:36.429 --> 00:01:41.017
THE INVINCIBLE SAMURAI

5
00:01:42.018 --> 00:01:43.853
I trust you've been well.

6
00:01:43.937 --> 00:01:46.523
It's been far too long. Mr. Tokugawa.

7
00:01:47.398 --> 00:01:49.025
You look like you're doing well.

8
00:01:59.369 --> 00:02:02.038
Kyoichiro Sabu. ninth dan.

9
00:02:02.622 --> 00:02:03.790
Mr. Tokugawa.

10
00:02:03.873 --> 00:02:06.292
Dan? What's that?

11
00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:09.629
I guess you wouldn't know what that means.

12
00:02:09.712 --> 00:02:11.464
He's been called "Sabu the Killer."

13
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:14.676
Of course. his skill pales
in comparison to your own. sir.

14
00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:15.802
Mr. Tokugawa.

15
00:02:16.469 --> 00:02:17.512
Rumors suggest

16
00:02:17.595 --> 00:02:20.515
he may have even cut down
more than 20 people.

17
00:02:20.598 --> 00:02:21.808
Mr. Tokugawa!

18
00:02:23.893 --> 00:02:26.729
In today's Japan.
or even the world at large.

19
00:02:26.813 --> 00:02:31.734
no one has slain as many with a sword
as the man who stands before you now.

20
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:32.819
Mr. Tokugawa!

21
00:02:33.444 --> 00:02:36.573
Oh. Is something bothering you. Mr. Sabu?

22
00:02:37.323 --> 00:02:38.658
Who is this person?

23
00:02:39.159 --> 00:02:42.287
What do your senses tell you. Kyoichiro?

24
00:02:42.829 --> 00:02:45.081
What's going on here? Who is this?

25
00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:46.916
Who is this man?

26
00:02:47.917 --> 00:02:50.712
Have you forgotten
we agreed you wouldn't ask that?

27
00:02:50.795 --> 00:02:53.339
Everything will be explained
after the match.

28
00:02:53.423 --> 00:02:56.843
Mr. Tokugawa.
I'm not the type to break a promise.

29
00:02:56.926 --> 00:02:58.845
So I hope that you can forgive me.

30
00:02:59.721 --> 00:03:02.348
I'm afraid
I can no longer accept this match.

31
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:07.979
I may not be a young man anymore.
but I won't needlessly throw my life away.

32
00:03:08.062 --> 00:03:11.065
Oh. now this should prove
to be rather interesting.

33
00:03:11.149 --> 00:03:13.109
What makes you say something like that?

34
00:03:13.902 --> 00:03:17.614
Since I set foot in the ring.
it's happened six times already.

35
00:03:19.699 --> 00:03:20.699
Huh?

36
00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:23.119
Just now makes it seven.

37
00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:27.874
I've now been cut down by him
a full seven times in a row.

38
00:03:27.957 --> 00:03:30.126
You… you did what to him?

39
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:33.171
-The first strike I felt...
-Was Hachimonji.

40
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.340
Hachimonji?

41
00:03:35.423 --> 00:03:37.675
Yes. it's exactly as he said.

42
00:03:37.759 --> 00:03:39.886
What does that mean? Hachimon…

43
00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:43.264
I was cloven clean in two
from my head.

44
00:03:43.348 --> 00:03:44.933
Straight down through my torso.

45
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.810
Split through the center.
so my body became hachimonji.

46
00:03:47.894 --> 00:03:49.646
the Chinese character for eight.

47
00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:50.980
What?!

48
00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:53.399
The second of his strikes.

49
00:03:53.483 --> 00:03:54.484
The neck.

50
00:03:55.526 --> 00:03:57.403
You had left yourself wide open.

51
00:03:58.238 --> 00:04:00.406
The third attack was through the shoulder.

52
00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:02.492
Cutting all the way through.

53
00:04:02.992 --> 00:04:06.913
That's right.
And my body put up no resistance at all.

54
00:04:07.789 --> 00:04:09.415
As for the fourth attack.

55
00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.920
I came from the side.
severing your front half from the back.

56
00:04:14.504 --> 00:04:16.673
The fifth strike. across the chest.

57
00:04:16.756 --> 00:04:19.425
The sixth was a diagonal slash
across the body.

58
00:04:20.009 --> 00:04:22.178
And the last was across
the chest and shoulders.

59
00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:24.514
taking both arms along with it.

60
00:04:25.014 --> 00:04:26.891
Hmm…

61
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:28.977
I appreciate it.

62
00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:31.437
Your lack of resistance
made the victory easy.

63
00:04:32.063 --> 00:04:33.940
My lack of resistance?

64
00:04:34.023 --> 00:04:37.527
But that's… that's absurd!
I held nothing back.

65
00:04:39.028 --> 00:04:42.699
Even if it was just in my mind.
I gave it everything that I could.

66
00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:46.703
So you're telling me that was it?
The battle's already been fought?

67
00:04:47.328 --> 00:04:50.206
By just standing there.
you know the outcome already?

68
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.250
That's right. Mr. Tokugawa.

69
00:04:52.333 --> 00:04:54.168
Today's match has been settled.

70
00:04:54.252 --> 00:04:55.461
Seven to nothing.

71
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:57.964
But. uh. Mr. Miyamoto.

72
00:04:58.047 --> 00:04:59.882
you don't even have a sword.

73
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:03.720
How would you have been able
to cleave. split. or slash him?

74
00:05:06.055 --> 00:05:08.933
You're unable to cut someone
without a sword?

75
00:05:09.434 --> 00:05:10.727
Uh. Mr. Tokugawa.

76
00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:12.186
enough with this!

77
00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:13.813
Who is this Miyamoto?!

78
00:05:15.023 --> 00:05:17.567
Could it be your swords
are so inexpedient?

79
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:22.280
May I inspect it? The sword you carry?

80
00:05:22.363 --> 00:05:23.364
Huh?

81
00:05:23.448 --> 00:05:25.241
You want to see my sword?

82
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:28.244
Does that make you uneasy?

83
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:29.954
Oh. well… Well I. uh…

84
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:34.000
I suppose that would be all right.
since the match has already been settled.

85
00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:38.379
I would very much like to see
how Musashi holds a sword.

86
00:05:38.463 --> 00:05:40.506
In fact. I'm dying to see it.

87
00:05:41.382 --> 00:05:43.092
Then. here you go.

88
00:05:57.106 --> 00:05:59.025
What… what's he doing?

89
00:05:59.776 --> 00:06:02.278
Ah. yes. I've missed this feeling.

90
00:06:03.112 --> 00:06:04.030
Mr. Sabu.

91
00:06:04.113 --> 00:06:06.532
May I take a look at that one as well?

92
00:06:08.618 --> 00:06:11.371
One sword should be
shorter than the other.

93
00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.289
but yours are of equal length.

94
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:15.416
So. uh. Mr. Miyamoto.

95
00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:17.168
if it's not too much trouble.

96
00:06:17.251 --> 00:06:21.297
I wonder if maybe
you would show us your technique?

97
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:23.299
You want to see my technique?

98
00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:26.052
-Yes. If you don't mind.
-I'd like to see too.

99
00:06:26.886 --> 00:06:28.805
I would be happy to show you.

100
00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:31.891
But to give a proper demonstration.
I need to know something.

101
00:06:32.392 --> 00:06:34.227
Which one of you do I kill?

102
00:06:34.310 --> 00:06:35.812
No. no. no. no. no. no!

103
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:38.314
I'm only joking.

104
00:06:38.981 --> 00:06:42.110
It's beautifully finished.
but the metal of the blade

105
00:06:42.985 --> 00:06:45.238
hasn't been sufficiently tempered.

106
00:06:45.905 --> 00:06:48.574
This is not a sword you could kill with.

107
00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:05.174
See? I knew it.

108
00:07:05.675 --> 00:07:08.344
Huh? What the hell did he just do?

109
00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:11.848
Both blades are broken off
right at the hilt.

110
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:14.851
Although they may look convincing…

111
00:07:14.934 --> 00:07:15.935
Uh-huh.

112
00:07:17.103 --> 00:07:18.855
…they cannot be called swords.

113
00:07:19.689 --> 00:07:23.609
How do you expect them to kill
when they can't even withstand a swing?

114
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:25.611
Mr. Tokugawa.

115
00:07:25.695 --> 00:07:27.530
who the hell is this man?

116
00:07:27.613 --> 00:07:29.365
Where did this Miyamoto come from?

117
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:31.451
I've been a swordsman for over 60 years.

118
00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:34.871
Never once. have I heard of
a sword being broken with just a swing!

119
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:37.707
I demand to know who the hell you are!

120
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:42.628
My name is Musashi Miyamoto.
It's a pleasure.

121
00:07:45.214 --> 00:07:47.717
He is. uh. who he says he is.

122
00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:49.177
Don't be ridiculous!

123
00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:53.139
You've been mocking me from the start.
haven't you? What a day!

124
00:07:53.764 --> 00:07:57.935
Be it with a sword. a spear.
a bow. or even with my bare hands.

125
00:07:58.019 --> 00:07:59.645
I will defeat the strong.

126
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:03.649
The strongest man alive
is about to meet his match.

127
00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:09.197
I'm so excited. I can't stop shaking.

128
00:08:11.824 --> 00:08:12.658
What?!

129
00:08:12.742 --> 00:08:15.286
The strongest creature on Earth

130
00:08:15.369 --> 00:08:17.997
in hand-to-hand combat
against Japan's top brawler.

131
00:08:18.080 --> 00:08:21.417
It was a spectacular sight to see.
I couldn't believe it was happening.

132
00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:25.421
The kind of platinum card battle
no one could take issue with.

133
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:31.427
Oh man.

134
00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:33.846
Hanayama's really something. isn't he?

135
00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:36.933
Huh? Why does he get the recognition?

136
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:38.601
Because he knew.

137
00:08:38.684 --> 00:08:41.812
He knew he could save himself
if he went up against Yujiro.

138
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:46.943
He knew a fight like that would save him
from the endless boredom of everyday life.

139
00:08:47.026 --> 00:08:50.029
Well. looks like
you understand that much at least.

140
00:08:50.112 --> 00:08:53.449
Because he did go through with it
and squared off against the Ogre.

141
00:08:54.158 --> 00:08:55.952
Macho to the max.

142
00:08:56.035 --> 00:08:58.037
That's Hanayama for ya.

143
00:08:59.747 --> 00:09:01.457
-Hmm?
-Well. go on!

144
00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:05.270
He can't land an attack.
but the Ogre's not even moving.

145
00:09:05.294 --> 00:09:06.295
But how?

146
00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:09.549
The Ogre told Hanayama
his cells were shrinking back in fear.

147
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:10.967
even if he didn't know it.

148
00:09:11.050 --> 00:09:14.720
Yujiro said that?
Right to Hanayama's face?

149
00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:17.723
That day.
Hanayama made his finest rush.

150
00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:20.226
That day.
Hanayama threw his cleanest punch.

151
00:09:20.309 --> 00:09:22.228
And the Ogre invited him to attack first.

152
00:09:23.145 --> 00:09:25.731
His giant fist was inches away
from the Ogre's face.

153
00:09:26.315 --> 00:09:27.441
But in that instant.

154
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:30.361
the Ogre began powering up
one of his pocketed hands.

155
00:09:30.444 --> 00:09:31.737
and then freed his fist.

156
00:09:32.863 --> 00:09:34.615
Hanayama was hit head-on

157
00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:38.744
with the full force
of the Ogre's best "hand pocket" punch.

158
00:09:39.495 --> 00:09:43.249
To think. he took the brunt
of that kind of blow right to the face.

159
00:09:46.836 --> 00:09:48.170
Here. have a look at this.

160
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:50.631
Uh. where did this computer come from?

161
00:09:50.715 --> 00:09:54.677
This is footage captured
by a convenience store security camera.

162
00:09:55.886 --> 00:09:57.513
And that's Hanayama.

163
00:09:57.597 --> 00:09:59.932
It was a typical day for this shop

164
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:04.270
until all 350 pounds
of Hanayama came flying in.

165
00:10:04.353 --> 00:10:07.064
He took out four shelving units
along the way

166
00:10:07.148 --> 00:10:10.776
until the bento section in back
eventually broke his fall.

167
00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:12.111
Ah. man.

168
00:10:12.653 --> 00:10:15.531
That made him happy. I bet.
Must've been a relief.

169
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:19.744
You're not wrong there.
He was smiling quite contentedly.

170
00:10:23.873 --> 00:10:24.873
So.

171
00:10:25.374 --> 00:10:26.500
come on now.

172
00:10:26.584 --> 00:10:27.460
Hmm?

173
00:10:27.543 --> 00:10:29.795
-Who is it?
-Who are you talking about?

174
00:10:32.882 --> 00:10:35.551
The son of a bitch
on the other side of that door!

175
00:10:36.677 --> 00:10:39.055
Hmm.

176
00:10:39.138 --> 00:10:42.016
I can sense somebody
in the next room over.

177
00:10:42.516 --> 00:10:43.809
Who the hell are they?

178
00:10:43.893 --> 00:10:46.437
I'd expect nothing less.

179
00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:47.772
But. Baki. you know.

180
00:10:47.855 --> 00:10:50.733
there are lots of different people
who work in this building.

181
00:10:50.816 --> 00:10:54.070
What's strange about someone
in the next room? It happens all the time.

182
00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:58.574
Look. I know you don't think
I'm really that stupid.

183
00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:01.035
I am the son of Yujiro Hanma.

184
00:11:01.535 --> 00:11:03.287
There is something in that room.

185
00:11:03.371 --> 00:11:05.247
Are they a man or a woman?

186
00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:08.084
Maybe there's more than one.
Are they even human?

187
00:11:08.584 --> 00:11:11.545
And what about their strength?
Are they weak or powerful?

188
00:11:12.046 --> 00:11:15.091
Are they here to try and kill me.
or just to intimidate me?

189
00:11:16.175 --> 00:11:19.845
Either way. there is something
on the other side of that door.

190
00:11:20.554 --> 00:11:22.348
Well. go on. then. Let me hear it.

191
00:11:22.431 --> 00:11:25.267
Who do you think is?

192
00:11:27.436 --> 00:11:29.105
Huh?

193
00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:33.109
How the hell should I know?
This ain't a movie. man.

194
00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:36.112
-So you were bluffing?
-Maybe.

195
00:11:36.195 --> 00:11:40.616
I mean. I'd be a real dimwit if I couldn't
sense a presence like that. Right?

196
00:11:54.296 --> 00:11:55.381
It's…

197
00:11:55.965 --> 00:11:57.049
It's him!

198
00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:01.137
When they looked at each other.
they each had a vision.

199
00:12:02.263 --> 00:12:05.641
One saw a giant mushroom cloud.
while the other

200
00:12:06.308 --> 00:12:10.396
saw a vast banquet that spread before them
and out to the horizon.

201
00:12:10.479 --> 00:12:14.650
You've got good instincts.
You impress me. boy. Are you a ninja?

202
00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:17.903
What is it. Baki?
Tell me what you're sensing.

203
00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:21.282
How does he make you feel?
What does he make you think?

204
00:12:22.742 --> 00:12:25.661
This might sound a little crazy. Or a lot.

205
00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:28.414
Oh. all right. Go on. say it.

206
00:12:29.081 --> 00:12:30.249
There's no way.

207
00:12:30.332 --> 00:12:33.043
Just trust your gut.
Come on. it's common sense.

208
00:12:33.127 --> 00:12:36.255
You know what you know.
The man who died hundreds of years ago?

209
00:12:36.338 --> 00:12:38.382
I know! They're all the same.

210
00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:41.927
There's just no other way to say it.

211
00:12:43.179 --> 00:12:44.680
Musashi Miyamoto?

212
00:12:44.764 --> 00:12:47.433
What? Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

213
00:12:47.516 --> 00:12:50.436
Baki. do you hear yourself?
Are you losing your mind?

214
00:12:51.353 --> 00:12:52.980
Am I going insane?

215
00:12:53.564 --> 00:12:55.691
Trust me. I asked myself that too.

216
00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:57.777
I'm not crazy. but…

217
00:12:58.903 --> 00:13:00.613
Let me see if I got this straight.

218
00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:03.491
If what I think is happening is happening.

219
00:13:03.574 --> 00:13:06.535
a dead samurai has been
brought back to life in the present.

220
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:09.705
Even terrible B-movies
have better plots than that.

221
00:13:09.789 --> 00:13:12.958
You… you really do
understand the situation.

222
00:13:13.042 --> 00:13:16.295
Honestly. I think it's less
about what I understand

223
00:13:16.378 --> 00:13:18.339
and more about what I feel.

224
00:13:18.923 --> 00:13:19.965
I…

225
00:13:20.049 --> 00:13:21.300
I jumped.

226
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.303
Oh?

227
00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:28.849
You still got me.

228
00:13:28.933 --> 00:13:31.352
Actually. you dodged the attack.

229
00:13:32.061 --> 00:13:33.854
An excellent move. boy.

230
00:13:34.522 --> 00:13:37.650
Look. Tokugawa. I can't explain it

231
00:13:37.733 --> 00:13:39.819
and it defies all logic and reason.

232
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:42.947
but I am convinced
beyond a shadow of a doubt.

233
00:13:43.030 --> 00:13:44.406
Even without evidence.

234
00:13:44.490 --> 00:13:46.867
That's all right.
I don't need you to prove it to me.

235
00:13:47.952 --> 00:13:49.870
This man is Musashi Miyamoto.

236
00:13:52.164 --> 00:13:53.624
The thing is…

237
00:13:53.707 --> 00:13:56.043
You're acting awfully suspicious.

238
00:13:56.544 --> 00:13:58.379
Is it because I hit the nail on the head?

239
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:01.965
Boy.

240
00:14:03.425 --> 00:14:05.302
Shall we take this outside?

241
00:14:10.099 --> 00:14:12.893
Which one?
Which one is stronger?

242
00:14:12.977 --> 00:14:14.228
All right. then.

243
00:14:14.311 --> 00:14:16.689
This will be as good a place as any
for a fight.

244
00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:18.899
You'll fight unarmed?

245
00:14:18.983 --> 00:14:21.402
Aren't you… unarmed?

246
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:24.405
Huh… Is that what you think?

247
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:27.992
I mean. sure doesn't look like
he has a weapon to me.

248
00:14:35.332 --> 00:14:36.417
How about now?

249
00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:37.793
Whoa!

250
00:14:39.545 --> 00:14:40.796
Can you see it?

251
00:14:43.507 --> 00:14:45.801
Where the hell did that thing come from?

252
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:48.429
There you have it.

253
00:14:49.763 --> 00:14:51.515
Do you understand?

254
00:14:51.599 --> 00:14:53.434
There's no one stronger than I am.

255
00:14:53.517 --> 00:14:55.936
Huh? Holy shit!

256
00:14:56.020 --> 00:14:58.689
Are they really gonna fight
right here. right now?

257
00:14:58.772 --> 00:15:03.193
When you reach my level of skill.
your body itself becomes like a blade.

258
00:15:03.777 --> 00:15:05.946
There's no longer a need to carry a sword.

259
00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:08.282
Wait. both of you.

260
00:15:08.365 --> 00:15:09.909
Well. what do you think?

261
00:15:09.992 --> 00:15:11.952
You think you can take me unarmed?

262
00:15:12.036 --> 00:15:13.203
Baki. don't!

263
00:15:14.038 --> 00:15:15.205
I had no idea…

264
00:15:16.081 --> 00:15:18.584
This kind of power even existed.

265
00:15:19.543 --> 00:15:20.711
Okay.

266
00:15:22.338 --> 00:15:23.464
Let's go.

267
00:15:23.547 --> 00:15:26.425
You two are really planning on doing this?

268
00:15:26.508 --> 00:15:29.053
Right here? Just like that?

269
00:15:29.553 --> 00:15:32.222
A battle like this just going to waste?

270
00:15:33.307 --> 00:15:35.225
Huh. is that what you think?

271
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:36.226
Well…

272
00:15:36.310 --> 00:15:39.063
Boy. do you think it's a waste?

273
00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:41.231
You wanna know what I think?

274
00:15:42.650 --> 00:15:45.986
You got me out here.
It'll only be a waste if we don't fight.

275
00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:47.821
-Mr. Tokugawa.
-Hmm?

276
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:50.324
This boy you've brought me. Who is he?

277
00:15:50.407 --> 00:15:53.494
Mr. Musashi.
if you remember. I made you a promise.

278
00:15:55.079 --> 00:15:55.996
Musashi?

279
00:15:56.080 --> 00:15:57.080
Ah.

280
00:15:57.498 --> 00:16:00.292
So then. this boy is
the strongest man in the country?

281
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:03.295
I'm actually curious
to hear your evaluation.

282
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:05.506
Go on.
what do you think of this young man?

283
00:16:05.589 --> 00:16:06.632
Hmm…

284
00:16:08.092 --> 00:16:09.343
All right. then.

285
00:16:09.426 --> 00:16:12.763
I don't think either Arima or Akiyama
would give him trouble.

286
00:16:12.846 --> 00:16:15.265
Hmm… He'll do. I suppose.

287
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:18.226
Oh!

288
00:16:21.730 --> 00:16:24.650
Are you from Ryukyu?

289
00:16:24.733 --> 00:16:27.236
I haven't fought anyone from there yet.

290
00:16:27.736 --> 00:16:31.573
But I've heard tell of a martial art
from that island chain that uses kicks.

291
00:16:37.037 --> 00:16:38.664
It's a curious technique.

292
00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:41.959
It seems disadvantageous
to make yourself unstable

293
00:16:42.042 --> 00:16:44.420
by standing on one leg during a fight.

294
00:16:47.756 --> 00:16:49.133
You may be a child.

295
00:16:49.758 --> 00:16:53.178
but you are not unskilled.
and this is a battle after all.

296
00:16:58.017 --> 00:17:00.686
Let's find out if he'll break.

297
00:17:13.449 --> 00:17:14.533
Baki…

298
00:17:15.576 --> 00:17:18.704
Turns out.
he's stronger than the average sword.

299
00:17:30.549 --> 00:17:31.592
Huh?

300
00:17:32.468 --> 00:17:34.678
Oh. yeah. That's right.

301
00:17:37.973 --> 00:17:39.641
I lost.

302
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:41.101
He got me good.

303
00:17:43.645 --> 00:17:48.067
Damn. words like "strong"
don't even come close to describing it.

304
00:17:51.945 --> 00:17:54.448
You can barely even call it a fight.

305
00:17:56.075 --> 00:17:58.077
-Huh?
-It was at that moment…

306
00:17:58.160 --> 00:17:59.495
Hold on!

307
00:18:00.079 --> 00:18:02.581
He had just then
come to the realization

308
00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:06.960
that he had fought a historical swordsman
of legendary skill.

309
00:18:07.461 --> 00:18:09.254
Naturally. he was perplexed.

310
00:18:09.755 --> 00:18:12.716
I mean. come on.
There ain't no way. That's totally nuts.

311
00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:15.511
Musashi Miyamoto?

312
00:18:15.594 --> 00:18:17.721
Who has been dead for centuries?!

313
00:18:17.805 --> 00:18:20.015
But the pain he felt
in his head and body

314
00:18:20.099 --> 00:18:21.767
confirmed this reality.

315
00:18:21.850 --> 00:18:24.645
An experience that defied all logic.

316
00:18:27.731 --> 00:18:28.982
I gotta see him again!

317
00:18:30.567 --> 00:18:31.985
Oh!

318
00:18:32.653 --> 00:18:33.737
There you are.

319
00:18:34.613 --> 00:18:35.613
Oh. hey.

320
00:18:36.198 --> 00:18:38.742
He's really here. Musashi Miyamoto!

321
00:18:38.826 --> 00:18:41.245
You're just in time. Join us.

322
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:43.997
We're about to start some training.

323
00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:47.751
This bamboo was freshly cut
from the garden this morning.

324
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:50.504
Huh? Wait. I've heard about this.

325
00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:55.509
Musashi could apparently shred
freshly-cut bamboo with just one swing.

326
00:18:56.301 --> 00:18:58.262
The wind pressure. His grip.

327
00:18:59.304 --> 00:19:00.389
It was so strong

328
00:19:00.472 --> 00:19:04.143
that he could actually crush
every node in a stalk of bamboo.

329
00:19:10.315 --> 00:19:12.651
You gotta be kidding me?!
Two at the same time?

330
00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:18.907
Look at the way he's holding it.

331
00:19:34.256 --> 00:19:36.091
He splintered the bamboo.

332
00:19:36.592 --> 00:19:39.678
One after another.
the poles that had been prepared for him…

333
00:19:40.846 --> 00:19:43.473
…were smashed to pieces
as if they were nothing at all.

334
00:19:44.224 --> 00:19:45.809
Almost unwillingly.

335
00:19:46.393 --> 00:19:48.812
the words bubbled up to the boy's lips.

336
00:19:49.771 --> 00:19:51.315
-Musashi.
-Hmm?

337
00:19:52.482 --> 00:19:54.568
Tell me. what is
the purpose of this training?

338
00:19:57.070 --> 00:19:58.822
What is its purpose?

339
00:19:59.448 --> 00:20:01.825
Honestly.
I've never thought about it that way.

340
00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:08.081
Put simply. training is training.
and it's what a proper swordsman must do.

341
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:11.585
In other words… you do it so you can win.

342
00:20:11.668 --> 00:20:14.504
Yes. That goes without saying.

343
00:20:15.130 --> 00:20:18.091
Then. wouldn't fighting me
make for even better training?

344
00:20:20.844 --> 00:20:21.845
Listen. boy.

345
00:20:22.679 --> 00:20:24.848
It would be fair to say
you're already dead.

346
00:20:25.432 --> 00:20:26.850
For some time.

347
00:20:26.934 --> 00:20:29.478
you were completely knocked out
and defenseless.

348
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:31.855
How many times do you think
I could've killed you?

349
00:20:32.773 --> 00:20:34.441
His fighting philosophy.

350
00:20:34.524 --> 00:20:37.110
it was completely different
from the boy's.

351
00:20:37.194 --> 00:20:41.073
which left Baki feeling ashamed
of his suggestion for a rematch.

352
00:20:41.573 --> 00:20:43.700
Yeah. I guess you're right.

353
00:20:46.370 --> 00:20:48.872
Why don't you give it a try? Go on.

354
00:20:48.956 --> 00:20:50.207
Hmm?

355
00:20:53.919 --> 00:20:57.881
Is there some kind of problem?
I'd like to see your form. young man.

356
00:21:02.469 --> 00:21:03.887
Oh!

357
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:06.390
Oh!

358
00:21:07.057 --> 00:21:10.894
And right through the node. at that.
That's not easy to accomplish.

359
00:21:10.978 --> 00:21:12.479
More impressively.

360
00:21:14.022 --> 00:21:16.149
you executed the move faster this time.

361
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:17.150
Much faster.

362
00:21:17.234 --> 00:21:21.655
I told you. didn't I?
Baki is the strongest kid on the planet.

363
00:21:22.447 --> 00:21:25.409
He's fast. yes. but he's no warrior.

364
00:21:28.662 --> 00:21:30.414
And with that. Tokugawa.

365
00:21:30.497 --> 00:21:31.790
Yes?

366
00:21:31.873 --> 00:21:32.874
I'll be going out.

367
00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:34.167
What now?

368
00:21:34.251 --> 00:21:38.171
What are
you talking about. Mr. Musashi?

369
00:21:38.255 --> 00:21:40.632
You know that I'm eager
to see more of this world.

370
00:21:40.716 --> 00:21:42.259
is there something wrong with that?

371
00:21:42.342 --> 00:21:45.012
It's not that at all!
It's just that it's impossible.

372
00:21:45.095 --> 00:21:47.139
You can't go out
into the world unaccompanied.

373
00:21:47.222 --> 00:21:49.182
You're not ready. You'll get into trouble.

374
00:21:49.266 --> 00:21:53.186
What kind of trouble could I get into?
Do I look like a child?

375
00:21:53.270 --> 00:21:55.689
-It's not gonna happen.
-Huh?

376
00:21:56.481 --> 00:21:58.442
You can forget about going out right now.

377
00:21:59.026 --> 00:22:00.027
Hmm?

378
00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:02.946
You're far too naive.

379
00:22:03.905 --> 00:22:05.699
You said I should already be dead.

380
00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:07.701
but you didn't finish me off!

381
00:22:08.952 --> 00:22:10.672
Whether
it's modern martial arts.

382
00:22:10.704 --> 00:22:13.206
fighting sports. or combat disciplines.

383
00:22:13.790 --> 00:22:16.960
the fastest move in all of them
is the jab.

384
00:22:17.711 --> 00:22:20.589
I am faster
than the speed of light!

385
00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:35.455
♪ Yeah ♪

386
00:23:35.539 --> 00:23:37.999
♪ Yeah. yeah ♪

387
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.710
♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah ♪

388
00:23:41.586 --> 00:23:44.214
♪ Yeah. yeah ♪

389
00:23:44.714 --> 00:23:46.758
♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah ♪

389
